# Dart Code Style Guidelines

## General Style
- Follow Flutter's style guide and best practices
- Use camelCase for variables and methods
- Use PascalCase for classes and enums
- Keep methods short and focused on a single responsibility
- Add appropriate comments for complex logic

## UI Components
- Create reusable widgets for common UI elements
- Use the glass_card_widget for frosted glass effect components
- Follow the app's color scheme defined in app_colors.dart
- Maintain consistent text styles from app_text_styles.dart

## Models
- Create immutable model classes with final fields
- Implement toString(), ==, and hashCode for all model classes
- Include factory constructors for JSON serialization/deserialization
- Do not use freezed package or part syntax

## State Management
- Use setState for state management
- Keep widget state localized when possible
- Use controllers for complex state logic

## Data Storage
- Use shared_preferences for simple data storage
- Implement proper error handling for all I/O operations